# localStorage Design Rules

## Tasks must be saved/loaded

- Save:

```js
localStorage.setItem("tasks", JSON.stringify(tasks));
```

- Load:

```js
const tasks = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("tasks")) || [];
```

## Auto-save triggers

Must auto-save on every mutation:

- add task
- edit task
- update progress

## Data integrity rules

- Always validate/normalize loaded tasks (handle missing fields).
- Never crash if storage is empty/corrupt; fall back to defaults.

